Third-party dependencies
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

Príncipe stands on the shoulders of many open-source projects. The full
list of npm and pip dependencies is in apps/principe/package.json and
services/statistician/requirements.txt; the licenses for each are
fetched at install time and surfaced in node_modules/<pkg>/LICENSE
and site-packages/<pkg>-*.dist-info/.

Notable AGPL-compatible runtime dependencies whose presence is
load-bearing for Príncipe's functionality:

  • Next.js                  MIT             https://nextjs.org
  • React                    MIT             https://react.dev
  • Prisma                   Apache-2.0      https://prisma.io
  • Tailwind CSS             MIT             https://tailwindcss.com
  • SimpleWebAuthn           MIT             https://simplewebauthn.dev
  • Anthropic SDK            MIT             https://github.com/anthropics/anthropic-sdk-typescript
  • PostgreSQL               PostgreSQL      https://postgresql.org
  • FastAPI                  MIT             https://fastapi.tiangolo.com
  • PyMC                     Apache-2.0      https://pymc.io
  • NumPyro                  Apache-2.0      https://num.pyro.ai
  • NumPy                    BSD-3-Clause    https://numpy.org
  • Pandas                   BSD-3-Clause    https://pandas.pydata.org
  • Pydantic                 MIT             https://pydantic.dev

Vendored packages under packages/:
  packages/rbac, packages/theme, packages/telemetry — first-party
  code authored by the Príncipe project, distributed under AGPL-3.0
  along with the rest of this repository.

