Knowledge corpus
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

The calibration/ directory contains structured summaries derived from
publicly available CISO-research sources (industry surveys, regulator
guidance, vendor reports). Citations live alongside each entry. No
proprietary, paywalled, or licensed-redistribution-only content is
bundled in this repository.

If you spot something that shouldn't be there, please file a security
issue via SECURITY.md.

═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
The 1919 plate
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

The eclipse photograph in apps/principe/public/ depicts the May 29,
1919 total solar eclipse observed from the island of Príncipe by Arthur
Eddington's expedition — the observation that proved general relativity.
The plate is in the public domain.
